From 79c40ad90b9a82360ebdd59bd8a28c484b332adb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Andre Mauricio Zelak <andre.zelak@windriver.com>
Date: Mon, 25 May 2026 14:54:10 -0300
Subject: [PATCH 06/11] HA monitoring and control socket

Adds a communication socket to phc2sys, and commands to monitor
HA status and control HA parameters.

The new configuration option ha_phc2sys_com_socket can be used to
rename the socket. The default socket path is /var/run/phc2sys-phc-inst1.

List of Commands:

status

The 'status' command shows the current HA status in table format,
containing the current status of all configured clock sources, and
an indication of which clock is current select.

The * sign marks the current source clock.
The - sign marks the active candidate clock, waiting for the stability
timer to assume source role.
The x sign marks the disable clock sources (see 'disable source' command)

clock source

The 'clock source' command shows the current source clock, indicated by
its interface name.

forced lock

The 'forced lock' command returns "True" string if the Best Clock Available
Selection Algorithm is disabled, and a clock is locked as source.

enable lock

The 'enable lock' command configures one clock is to act as the sole source,
and disables the Best Clock Available Selection Algorithm.

It receives the interface name as parameter, ie 'enable lock enp81s0f0'.

disable lock

The 'disable lock' command removes the configuration done by 'enable lock',
and re-enables the selection algorithm.

enable source and disable source

The 'disable source' command can be used to remove one source clock from
the selection algorithm, unless it is the last. If the active clock is
disabled, it will be forced out, and a new source will be selected.

The command 'enable source' re-enables the clock to be selected.

valid sources

The 'valid sources' command returns a list of all sources that are currently
matching the HA requirements, the one selected as source and the other that
are in stand by. The list contains the clock's interface name.

